Name: tcapServerSysUp
Description: Indicates that the TCAP Server is up and active.

Name: tcapServerSysDown
Description: Indicates that the TCAP Server is shutting down.

Name: tcapServerDBConnStatus
Description: Indicates the change in connection status of the database server.

Name: tcapServerBusConnStatus
Description: Indicates the change in availability status of message complex.

Name: tcapServerMsgQThresholdStatus
Description: Indicates that the number of messages in the message queue has reached the threshold value.

Name: tcapServerSS7ReadNullMsgStatus
Description: Indicates whether SS7 card read on the given queue is failing.

Name: tcapServerEnDecodesThresholdStatus
Description: Indicates the growth of encoding/decoding failures wrt incoming messages.

Name: tcapServerDefaultActsThresholdStatus
Description: Indicates the growth of default actions taken wrt incoming messages.

Name: tcapServerTrapsResync
Description: Indicates the start and end of a trap resync operation.

Name: tcapServerHeartbeat
Description: Sent periodically to indicate that Tcap Server is alive

Name: tcapServerNoDlgThresholdStatus
Description: Indicates that there was no free dialog available for incoming transaction
